  "prompt": "Why do I urinate after a meal?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why you might urinate after a meal:\n\n1. Normal digestive process\n- Eating stimulates digestion and metabolism\n- Can trigger increased kidney function and urine production\n- Known as the gastrocolic reflex\n\n2. Hydration intake\n- If you drink fluids with your meal\n- Increased liquid consumption leads to more frequent urination\n\n3. Caffeine consumption\n- Coffee and tea are diuretics\n- Can increase urine production after meals\n\n4. Potential medical conditions\n- Diabetes\n- Overactive bladder\n- Irritable bowel syndrome\n- Prostate issues (in men)\n\n5. Hormonal influences\n- Certain hormones are released during digestion\n- Can affect kidney function and urine production\n\n6. Food and drink types\n- Some foods and beverages have diuretic properties\n- Alcohol, citrus fruits, watermelon can increase urination\n\nIf frequent urination after meals is persistent, uncomfortable, or accompanied by other symptoms, it's recommended to consult a healthcare professional for proper evaluation.",
